name: Push-Up
instructions: Start in a plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor.
Push back up to the starting position.
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement.

name: Barbell Squat
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and barbell resting on your upper back.
Lower your body by bending your knees and hips.
Descend until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
instructions: Sit or stand with a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height.
Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height.
Keep your core tight throughout the exercise.

name: Bent-Over Row
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell.
Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight.
Pull the barbell towards your torso.
Lower the barbell back to the starting position.

name: Plank
instructions: Start in a forearm plank position.
Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels.
Engage your core and hold the position.
Avoid letting your hips sag.

name: Lunges
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Step forward with one leg and lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Push back to the starting position.
Alternate legs with each repetition.

name: Jumping Jacks
instructions: Stand with feet together and arms at your sides.
Jump up, spreading your legs and raising your arms overhead.
Return to the starting position.
Repeat continuously at a steady pace.

name: Deadlift
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell over mid-foot.
Bend at the hips and knees to grip the barbell.
Lift the barbell by extending your hips and knees.
Lower the barbell back to the ground with control.

name: Bicep Curl
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Curl the weights up towards your shoulders.
Lower the weights back to the starting position.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout.

name: Tricep Dips
instructions: Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with hands beside your hips.
Slide your buttocks off the edge, supporting your weight with your hands.
Lower your body by bending your elbows.
Push back up to the starting position.

name: Mountain Climbers
instructions: Start in a high plank position.
Drive one knee towards your chest.
Quickly switch legs, driving the other knee towards your chest.
Continue alternating legs at a fast pace.

name: Russian Twists
instructions: Sit on the floor with knees bent and feet lifted.
Lean back slightly and clasp your hands together.
Twist your torso to one side, then the other.
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement.

name: Burpees
instructions: Start standing, then drop into a squat with hands on the floor.
Kick your feet back into a plank position.
Perform a push-up, then jump your feet back to the squat position.
Explode up into a jump, reaching your arms overhead.

name: Leg Press
instructions: Sit on the leg press machine with feet shoulder-width apart on the platform.
Push the platform away by extending your legs.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Keep your knees aligned with your toes throughout.

name: Pull-Up
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip.
Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar.
Lower yourself back to the starting position.
Avoid swinging or using momentum.

name: Seated Row
instructions: Sit on the rowing machine with feet secured.
Pull the handle towards your torso, keeping elbows close to your body.
Return to the starting position.
Maintain a straight back throughout the exercise.

name: Chest Fly
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended above your chest.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc.
Bring the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout.

name: Leg Curl
instructions: Lie face down on the leg curl machine.
Position the pad just above your ankles.
Curl your legs towards your buttocks.
Slowly return to the starting position.

name: Calf Raise
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.
Raise your heels off the ground, standing on your toes.
Lower your heels back to the ground.
Perform the movement slowly and with control.

name: Side Plank
instructions: Lie on your side with legs extended.
Prop yourself up on one forearm, lifting your hips off the ground.
Hold the position, keeping your body in a straight line.
Switch sides and repeat.

name: High Knees
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Run in place, lifting your knees as high as possible.
Keep your core engaged and back straight.
Move your arms in rhythm with your legs.

name: Lat Pulldown
instructions: Sit at the lat pulldown machine and grasp the bar with a wide grip.
Pull the bar down towards your chest.
Slowly return the bar to the starting position.
Keep your back straight and avoid leaning back.

name: Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Stand or sit with a dumbbell held with both hands overhead.
Lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbows.
Extend your arms to return to the starting position.
Keep your elbows close to your head throughout.

name: Box Jump
instructions: Stand in front of a sturdy box or platform.
Jump onto the box, landing softly with knees slightly bent.
Step or jump back down to the starting position.
Use your arms to help propel you upwards.

name: Bicycle Crunch
instructions: Lie on your back with hands behind your head.
Lift your shoulders off the ground and bring one knee towards your chest.
Twist your torso to bring the opposite elbow towards the knee.
Alternate sides in a pedaling motion.

name: Bench Press
instructions: Lie on a bench with feet flat on the ground.
Grip the barbell with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Lower the barbell to your chest.
Press the barbell back up to the starting position.

name: Jump Rope
instructions: Hold the jump rope handles with elbows close to your sides.
Swing the rope over your head and jump as it passes your feet.
Maintain a steady rhythm and jump on the balls of your feet.
Keep your core engaged and posture upright.

name: Side Lunge
instructions: Stand with feet together.
Step to the side with one leg, bending the knee while keeping the other leg straight.
Push back to the starting position.
Alternate sides with each repetition.

name: Reverse Fly
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight.
Raise the dumbbells out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.

name: Leg Raise
instructions: Lie on your back with legs extended.
Lift your legs towards the ceiling, keeping them straight.
Lower your legs back to the starting position without touching the ground.
Engage your core throughout the movement.

name: Treadmill Run
instructions: Set the treadmill to a comfortable running speed.
Run at a steady pace, maintaining good posture.
Keep your core engaged and arms moving naturally.
Cool down by gradually reducing the speed.

name: Cable Tricep Pushdown
instructions: Stand facing the cable machine with a rope attachment.
Grip the rope with both hands and pull it down.
Extend your arms fully, then return to the starting position.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout.

name: Goblet Squat
instructions: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both hands.
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.
Lower your body into a squat, keeping the dumbbell close.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.

name: Incline Bench Press
instructions: Lie on an incline bench with feet flat on the ground.
Grip the barbell with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Lower the barbell to your upper chest.
Press the barbell back up to the starting position.

name: Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.
Raise your heels off the ground, standing on your toes.
Lower your heels back to the ground.
Perform the movement slowly and with control.

name: Kettlebell Swing
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell with both hands.
Hinge at the hips and swing the kettlebell between your legs.
Thrust your hips forward to swing the kettlebell up to shoulder height.
Control the swing back down and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Raise the dumbbells out to the sides until they reach shoulder height.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout.

name: Crunch
instructions: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the ground.
Place your hands behind your head.
Lift your shoulders off the ground, engaging your core.
Lower back to the starting position.

name: Elliptical Trainer
instructions: Step onto the elliptical and select a comfortable resistance level.
Move your feet in a smooth, circular motion.
Use the handles to engage your upper body.
Maintain a steady pace and good posture.

name: Cable Bicep Curl
instructions: Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attachment.
Grip the bar with palms facing up.
Curl the bar towards your shoulders.
Lower the bar back to the starting position.

name: Step-Up
instructions: Stand in front of a box or platform.
Step up onto the box with one foot.
Bring the other foot up to meet the first.
Step back down and repeat, alternating legs.

name: Seated Leg Extension
instructions: Sit on the leg extension machine with your feet under the pad.
Extend your legs until they are straight.
Lower back to the starting position.
Keep your back against the seat throughout.

name: Dumbbell Chest Press
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand.
Press the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the dumbbells back to chest level.
Keep your feet flat on the ground throughout.

name: Rowing Machine
instructions: Sit on the rowing machine with feet secured.
Grip the handle with both hands.
Push with your legs and pull the handle towards your chest.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

name: Standing Overhead Press
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder height.
Press the barbell overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the barbell back to shoulder height.
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement.

name: Hanging Leg Raise
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar with arms extended.
Lift your legs towards your chest, keeping them straight.
Lower your legs back to the starting position.
Avoid swinging and use controlled movements.

name: Battle Ropes
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a rope in each hand.
Move your arms up and down to create waves in the ropes.
Maintain a steady rhythm and engage your core.
Continue for the desired duration.

name: Smith Machine Squat
instructions: Position the bar on your upper back and stand with feet shoulder-width apart.
Lower your body into a squat position.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Keep your back straight and core engaged.

name: Incline Dumbbell Fly
instructions: Lie on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand.
Extend your arms above your chest.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc.
Bring the dumbbells back to the starting position.

name: Reverse Crunch
instructions: Lie on your back with legs bent and feet flat on the ground.
Lift your legs towards your chest, curling your hips off the ground.
Lower your legs back to the starting position.
Engage your core throughout the movement.

name: Stationary Bike
instructions: Sit on the bike and adjust the seat height.
Start pedaling at a comfortable pace.
Maintain a steady rhythm and keep your back straight.
Increase resistance for added intensity.

name: Cable Lateral Raise
instructions: Stand next to a cable machine with the handle at the lowest setting.
Grip the handle with one hand and raise it out to the side.
Lower the handle back to the starting position.
Keep a slight bend in your elbow throughout.

name: Leg Press Machine
instructions: Sit on the leg press machine with feet shoulder-width apart on the platform.
Push the platform away by extending your legs.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Keep your knees aligned with your toes throughout.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell held with both hands above your chest.
Lower the dumbbell back over your head.
Return the dumbbell to the starting position.
Keep your arms slightly bent throughout.

name: Medicine Ball Slam
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball.
Raise the ball overhead with both hands.
Slam the ball down to the ground with force.
Catch the ball on the rebound and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Row
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand.
Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight.
Pull the dumbbell towards your torso.
Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.

name: Pec Deck Machine
instructions: Sit on the pec deck machine with arms at shoulder height.
Bring the handles together in front of your chest.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Keep your elbows slightly bent throughout.

name: Dumbbell Deadlift
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Bend at the hips and knees, lowering the dumbbells towards the ground.
Return to the starting position by extending your hips and knees.
Keep your back straight throughout the movement.

name: Treadmill Incline Walk
instructions: Set the treadmill to a moderate incline.
Walk at a steady pace, maintaining good posture.
Engage your core and swing your arms naturally.
Cool down by reducing the incline and speed.

name: Cable Chest Fly
instructions: Stand between two cable machines with handles at chest height.
Grip the handles and bring them together in front of your chest.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout.

name: Dumbbell Step-Up
instructions: Stand in front of a box or platform, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Step up onto the box with one foot.
Bring the other foot up to meet the first.
Step back down and repeat, alternating legs.

name: Tricep Kickback
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight.
Extend your arms behind you, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Return to the starting position.

name: Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Sit on the calf raise machine with feet on the platform.
Raise your heels by extending your ankles.
Lower your heels back to the starting position.
Keep the movement controlled throughout.

name: Barbell Curl
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip.
Curl the barbell towards your shoulders.
Lower the barbell back to the starting position.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout.

name: Elliptical Interval Training
instructions: Start with a warm-up at a moderate pace.
Increase the resistance and speed for 1 minute.
Return to the moderate pace for 2 minutes.
Repeat the intervals for the desired duration.

name: Cable Woodchop
instructions: Stand sideways to the cable machine with the handle set high.
Grip the handle with both hands and pull it diagonally across your body.
Return to the starting position.
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell Shrug
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Lift your shoulders towards your ears.
Lower your shoulders back to the starting position.
Keep your arms straight throughout the movement.

name: Cable Face Pull
instructions: Stand facing the cable machine with a rope attachment set at face height.
Grip the rope with both hands and pull it towards your face.
Return to the starting position.
Keep your elbows high and core engaged.

name: Reverse Lunge
instructions: Stand with feet together.
Step back with one leg and lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Push back to the starting position.
Alternate legs with each repetition.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand.
Press the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the dumbbells back to chest level.
Keep your feet flat on the ground throughout.

name: Barbell Bent-Over Row
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell.
Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight.
Pull the barbell towards your torso.
Lower the barbell back to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Raise the dumbbells in front of you until they reach shoulder height.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Keep your arms straight throughout the movement.

name: Cable Tricep Extension
instructions: Stand facing the cable machine with a rope attachment.
Grip the rope with both hands and pull it down.
Extend your arms fully, then return to the starting position.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with palms facing each other.
Curl the weights up towards your shoulders.
Lower the weights back to the starting position.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout.

name: Dumbbell Lunge
instructions: Stand with feet together, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Step forward with one leg and lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
Push back to the starting position.
Alternate legs with each repetition.

name: Cable Upright Row
instructions: Stand facing the cable machine with a straight bar attachment.
Grip the bar with palms facing down.
Pull the bar up towards your chin, keeping elbows higher than your wrists.
Lower the bar back to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Fly
instructions: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended above your chest.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc.
Bring the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout.

name: Barbell Deadlift
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell over mid-foot.
Bend at the hips and knees to grip the barbell.
Lift the barbell by extending your hips and knees.
Lower the barbell back to the ground with control.

name: Seated Dumbbell Press
instructions: Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height.
Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height.
Keep your core tight throughout the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Squat
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Lower your body into a squat position.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Keep your back straight and core engaged.

name: Barbell Bench Press
instructions: Lie on a bench with feet flat on the ground.
Grip the barbell with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Lower the barbell to your chest.
Press the barbell back up to the starting position.

name: Cable Crunch
instructions: Kneel in front of a cable machine with a rope attachment.
Grip the rope and pull it down towards your shoulders.
Crunch forward, engaging your core.
Return to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Lateral Lunge
instructions: Stand with feet together, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Step to the side with one leg, bending the knee while keeping the other leg straight.
Push back to the starting position.
Alternate sides with each repetition.

name: Barbell Overhead Press
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder height.
Press the barbell overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the barbell back to shoulder height.
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell Front Squat
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height.
Lower your body into a squat position.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Keep your back straight and core engaged.

name: Barbell Curl
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip.
Curl the barbell towards your shoulders.
Lower the barbell back to the starting position.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout.

name: Cable Chest Press
instructions: Stand between two cable machines with handles at chest height.
Grip the handles and press them forward until your arms are fully extended.
Return to the starting position.
Keep your core engaged throughout.

name: Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart holding a barbell in front of your thighs.
Hinge at the hips letting the bar travel down close to your legs while keeping a slight knee bend.
Lower until you feel a strong hamstring stretch without rounding your back.
Drive hips forward and squeeze glutes to return to the top.
Tips: Keep the bar close, maintain a neutral spine, move slowly on the descent.
Safety: Avoid excessive knee bend; stop if lumbar rounding occurs.

name: Walking Lunge
instructions: Stand tall holding dumbbells at your sides.
Step forward into a lunge creating two ~90 knee angles.
Push through the front heel and bring the rear leg forward into the next step.
Continue alternating steps maintaining upright torso.
Tips: Shorter steps emphasize quads; longer steps load glutes.
Safety: Keep knee tracking over toes; avoid crashing the rear knee into the floor.

name: Bulgarian Split Squat
instructions: Stand about two feet in front of a bench and place rear foot laces-down on top.
Descend by bending front knee keeping torso upright until front thigh is near parallel.
Drive through front heel to return to standing.
Repeat all reps then switch legs.
Tips: Slight forward torso lean can increase glute involvement.
Safety: Keep front knee tracking over mid-foot; avoid collapsing inward.

name: Incline Dumbbell Press
instructions: Set bench to a 2535 incline and sit with dumbbells resting on thighs.
Kick weights to start position with wrists stacked over elbows.
Lower dumbbells in a controlled arc to upper chest (not shoulders).
Press back up focusing on driving elbows inward slightly.
Tips: Keep shoulder blades retracted; avoid flaring elbows excessively.
Safety: Stop if shoulder discomfort; maintain neutral wrist alignment.

name: Farmer's Carry
instructions: Stand tall holding heavy dumbbells at your sides.
Brace core and walk controlled steps maintaining upright posture.
Avoid excessive sway; keep shoulder blades packed down and back.
Turn carefully and continue for prescribed distance or time.
Tips: Short, quick steps improve stability; think 'tall and tight'.
Safety: Do not allow weights to crash into legs; stop if grip fails.
